      • start

        public void start​(java.lang.String newName)
        Prints the Menu and starts a scanner to ask to the user for the menu option. The header of the Menu consists in the name of the menu. If there is some data or an header in the table, it will be printed. Having the option, this method calls the option callback.
        Parameters:
        newName - The string that represents the menu name.

      • start

        public void start()
        Prints the Menu and starts a scanner to ask to the user for the menu option. The header of the Menu consists in the name of the menu. If there is some data or an header in the table, it will be printed. If not, data lines will be printed if there are some. Having the option, this method calls the option callback.
